        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:56PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 556 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Indian Land, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Indian Land, Waxhaw, Marvin, Van Wyck, and Carolina Commons Shopping
Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
